laboratory_examinations.findings: NO ENTERIC GRAM NEGATIVE RODS FOUND. NO SALMONELLA OR SHIGELLA FOUND.

The appendix is markedly dilated up to 17 mm in caliber, fluid-filled with calcified appendicoliths at its base and tip, extensive adjacent inflammatory phlegmonous change involving the cecum and terminal ileum, numerous enlarged reactive ileocolic lymph nodes. No fluid collection, abscess, free intraperitoneal gas, or bowel obstruction.
